quest_title: The wavelength of first line of Lyman series of hydrogen is 1216\(\mathring{A}\). The wavelength of second member of Balmer series would be
explanation_txt:
\(\cfrac{1}{\lambda_{\mathrm{L}}}=\mathrm{R}\left[\cfrac{1}{1}-\cfrac{1}{4}\right]\)
or, \(\lambda_{\mathrm{L}}=\cfrac{4}{3 \mathrm{R}} \quad \ldots \ldots \ldots\) (i)
For Balmer series
\(\cfrac{1}{\lambda_{B}}=R\left[\cfrac{1}{4}-\cfrac{1}{16}\right]=\cfrac{3 R}{16}\)
\(\therefore \lambda_{B}=\cfrac{16}{3 R} \ldots \ldots \ldots \ldots\) (ii)
Dividing (ii) by (i)
\(\cfrac{\lambda_{\mathrm{B}}}{\lambda_{\mathrm{L}}}=\cfrac{\cfrac{16}{3 \mathrm{R}}}{3 \mathrm{R}}\)
\(\therefore \lambda_{\mathrm{B}}=4 \times 1216 \mathrm{A}\)

quest_title: A compound microscope with magnifying power 42 is to be constructed from two converging lenses of focal length 2cm and 5cm. The separation of lenses if final image is formed at 'D' is
explanation_txt:
\(\mathrm{m}=42, \mathrm{me}=1+\cfrac{\mathrm{D}}{\mathrm{f}_{\mathrm{e}}}=1+\cfrac{25}{5}=6\)

\(\therefore \mathrm{m}=\mathrm{m}_{\mathrm{o}} \times \mathrm{m}_{\mathrm{e}}\)

\(\dot{\mathrm{M}}_{\mathrm{o}}=42 / 6=7=\mathrm{v}_{\mathrm{d}} / \mathrm{u}_{\mathrm{o}}\)

or, \(\mathrm{V}_{\mathrm{o}}=7 \mathrm{u}_{\mathrm{o}}\)

\(\cfrac{1}{\mathrm{f}_{\mathrm{o}}}=\cfrac{1}{\mathrm{u}_{\mathrm{o}}}+\cfrac{1}{\mathrm{V}_{\mathrm{o}}}\)

or, \(\cfrac{1}{2}=\cfrac{1}{\mathrm{u}_{\mathrm{o}}}+\cfrac{1}{7 \mathrm{u}_{\mathrm{o}}}=\cfrac{7+1}{7 \mathrm{u}_{\mathrm{o}}}\)

\(\therefore\, \mathrm{u}_\mathrm{o}=16/7 \qquad \therefore\,\mathrm{v}_\mathrm{o}=16\,\text{cm}\)

For eye lens,

\(\mathrm{v}_{\mathrm{e}}=-25 \mathrm{cm} \quad \mathrm{f}_{\mathrm{e}}=5 \mathrm{cm}\)

\(\mathrm{u}_{\mathrm{e}}=\cfrac{\mathrm{f}_{\mathrm{e}} \mathrm{V}_{\mathrm{e}}}{\mathrm{V}_{\mathrm{e}}-\mathrm{f}_{\mathrm{e}}}=\cfrac{5(-25)}{-25-5}=4.2\)

\(\therefore \mathrm{L}=\mathrm{V}_{\mathrm{o}}+\mathrm{u}_{\mathrm{e}}=16+4.2=20.2 \mathrm{cm}\)
